From b52cba5a104cb35297b3149b6ded5bf6ed69db47 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 11:25:54 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 8: typed edge kinds (depends/extends/gates/verifies)

Chapter.dependsOn becomes an array of { id, kind } edges; the
prompt asks the model to pick the most specific relationship
kind for each dependency:

  - depends  - generic 'needs to land first' (neutral, solid)
  - extends  - builds on a primitive the other introduces (green)
  - gates    - hidden behind a flag/config (yellow, dashed 5 4)
  - verifies - tests / observability for the other (purple, dotted)

Storyboard renders each kind with its own stroke colour, dash
pattern, arrowhead colour, and label pill text. The header
gains a 4-entry legend; the detail-rail Connections section
shows the per-edge kind in each '<- gated by' / '-> verified by'
row.

Cache version bumped to v2 so v1 string-array caches are
silently dropped (next tour regenerates with typed edges). The
parser also accepts the old string form as a fallback, mapping
unknown shapes to kind='depends'.
